00:44.009 --> 00:45.384
Hey, space cadet!

00:46.186 --> 00:47.426
Your speech was awesome.

00:47.482 --> 00:49.538
No, it was hypocritical bullshit.

00:50.759 --> 00:52.264
Look at us, Will,

00:52.582 --> 00:55.742
we go to one of the most
expensive schools in Europe.

00:56.367 --> 00:58.577
Capitalism hasn't failed us.

00:58.754 --> 01:01.178
It's... empty rhetoric.

01:01.704 --> 01:03.113
Just words.

01:03.378 --> 01:04.674
You love words.

01:04.794 --> 01:06.098
What's up with you?

01:06.767 --> 01:08.415
Coach sick.

01:08.670 --> 01:10.828
Well, don't go baffing on me, Karl Marx.

01:13.063 --> 01:14.936
You wanna take a photo?

01:16.816 --> 01:18.423
Leave it, baby.

01:48.783 --> 01:49.933
Mr. Lorcan?

01:50.275 --> 01:51.612
What's going on, sir?

01:52.531 --> 01:54.822
Mr. Arn, why have we stopped?

01:58.021 --> 01:59.266
_

02:06.535 --> 02:08.068
Quiet, everybody.

02:09.499 --> 02:12.117
Shut the fuck up!

02:12.183 --> 02:15.831
My friends out there will shoot
anyone who tries to escape.

02:15.877 --> 02:18.669
Mr. Lorcan here is going
to collect your phones.

02:19.041 --> 02:21.180
Don't try playing the hero.

02:21.216 --> 02:22.170
Move!

02:24.202 --> 02:26.957
All right everybody, just stay calm.

02:31.662 --> 02:32.960
Where's the girl?

02:35.776 --> 02:37.192
Where is Chloe?

03:08.278 --> 03:09.640
Are you with the ICC?

03:09.650 --> 03:12.401
I'm Michel Dorn. I'm the
chief prosecutor of the court.

03:12.428 --> 03:14.266
Inspector Strand, this
is Inspector Costante.

03:14.285 --> 03:17.221
- Madam Ambassador.
- She tried to contact me from the coach.

03:17.231 --> 03:19.108
Just tell him we'll give
him whatever he wants.

03:19.131 --> 03:21.178
It's not in his interest
to hurt your daughter, OK?

03:21.196 --> 03:22.960
We'll do everything we
can to keep her safe.

03:23.823 --> 03:24.980
Inspector.

03:27.589 --> 03:30.000
This is Inspector Costante of the ICC.

03:30.010 --> 03:31.915
Who am I speaking to, please?

03:32.542 --> 03:33.976
He says he's going to kill us.

03:34.607 --> 03:35.900
What's your name, sweetheart?

03:36.020 --> 03:36.838
Chloe.

03:36.958 --> 03:39.127
Hey Chloe, I'm Marco.

03:39.161 --> 03:41.425
I'm here to make sure everybody stays safe.

03:41.440 --> 03:44.488
And I promise I'll do everything I can, OK?

03:44.779 --> 03:46.276
Do you trust me, Chloe?

03:46.553 --> 03:47.487
Yes.

03:47.516 --> 03:48.337
Good.

03:48.532 --> 03:49.956
You're being very brave.

03:50.076 --> 03:51.336
Now listen,

03:51.520 --> 03:53.445
if you can tell whoever's there

03:53.639 --> 03:55.535
this would be much better

03:55.655 --> 03:57.251
if we could speak directly.

03:58.431 --> 04:00.429
What took you so long?

04:00.463 --> 04:03.098
I've travelled from
Holland to be here, sir.

04:03.428 --> 04:05.115
Are you gonna tell me what's going on?

04:05.125 --> 04:07.084
One million Euros.

04:07.204 --> 04:08.163
Cash.

04:08.283 --> 04:11.604
For each of the hostages, or
I start blowing brains out.

04:12.105 --> 04:15.386
OK, it's going to take a
little time to get you that sum.

04:15.429 --> 04:16.935
You're stalling.

04:16.969 --> 04:19.629
Look, 15 million Euros is a lot of money.

04:19.652 --> 04:20.444
I've spoken to the bank,

04:20.459 --> 04:22.588
I can get the money
within a matter of hours.

04:22.597 --> 04:23.633
Listen to me,

04:23.637 --> 04:25.703
you'll get your money, OK?

04:28.868 --> 04:30.238
Sir, are you there?

04:35.702 --> 04:36.893
Get in there!

04:37.013 --> 04:38.201
Go!

